# CMD Commands #

"These are some Windows CMD commands I learned during my cybersecurity training."

--> Basic Commands

ipconfig = Displays the IP configuration of the system.

ipconfig /all = Displays detailed network information.

ping <IP_Address> = Checks connectivity with another device.

tracert <IP_Address> = Shows the path taken by packets.

nslookup <domain> = Finds the IP address of a domain.

netstat = Displays active network connections.

arp -a = Displays the ARP cache.

hostname = Displays the computer name.

whoami = Displays the current logged-in user.

systeminfo = Displays system information.

tasklist = Displays all running processes.

cls = Clears the command prompt screen.

exit = Closes the Command Prompt.
